<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="397" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[178,1085,803,1107]" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">
Di a g n o s i s: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wahis" authorityYear="2000" box="[374,542,902,923]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auranticornis">
<emphasis box="[374,542,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">F. auranticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique by the orange red antenna in combination with prolonged gena and head (behind eyes, dorsal view). The species shares the remaining colour pattern with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmid-Egger" authorityYear="2018" box="[494,710,960,982]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudodenticulata">
<emphasis box="[494,710,960,982]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">E. pseudodenticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taschenberg" authorityYear="1869" box="[763,907,960,982]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denticulata">
<emphasis box="[763,907,960,982]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">E. denticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is also a very small species with 
<quantity box="[374,432,990,1011]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
body length, whereas remaining species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmid-Egger" authorityYear="2018" box="[870,1085,989,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudodenticulata">
<emphasis box="[870,1085,989,1011]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="397">E. pseudodenticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
measueres at least 
<quantity box="[380,459,1019,1040]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
. See 
<bibRefCitation author="WAHIS R" box="[519,668,1019,1041]" journalOrPublisher="Not. faun" pageId="8" pageNumber="397" refId="ref10588" refString="WAHIS R. (2000): Hymenopteres aculeates du Yemen (Pompiliae, Vespidae). - Not. faun." title="Hymenopteres aculeates du Yemen (Pompiliae, Vespidae)" type="book" year="2000">WAHIS (2000)</bibRefCitation>
for detailed description. The female is undescribed.
</paragraph>
